The paper proposes a semi-supervised neural network model for multi-view problems, which involves learning representations of data from multiple views. This is a common problem in machine learning and can be applied to various subfields such as computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), multimedia (cs.MM), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed model also involves deep learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.MM.
